Explanation:

We create a graph to represent the dislikes between people. Then, we iterate over the graph to count the number of people with a dislike for each person. If we find any person with more than one dislike, we return false, as it is not possible to split the group into two. Otherwise, we return true.

The time complexity is O(n^2) because we iterate over all pairs of people. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a 2D array to store the graph. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only requires a small amount of energy to run.

